        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="TNYAdobeCaslonPro, 'Times New Roman', serif;" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="
              font-size: 24px;
              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 400;
              margin-top: 2px !important;
            ">
        23andMe privacy breach 
        </h2>  
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
              
          23andMe began as a mission to provide genetic testing that would enable people to learn about their ancestry. While 23andMe built the world’s largest DNA database with customer consent, many users weren’t fully aware their anonymized data could be <a 
style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #8C3321; color: black;" href="https://link.businesshistory.co/bh-28-06-2025-sold-or-used" target="_blank">sold or used</a> in pharmaceutical partnerships. Critics, including genetic counselors and ethicists, warned that delivering sensitive results without human consultation could lead to misinterpretation or psychological harm.

          </p>
        </mj-text> 

        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px 14px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.businesshistory.co/email/images/biopharma-investor- pullback-delays.jpg" alt="A rise in interest rates, coupled with the long time that it takes to see therapeutic R&D come to fruition, saw several investors take a step back from the biopharma scene." href="https://www.businesshistory.co" />
         <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;">
            <i>
           A rise in interest, coupled with delay in therapeutic R&D, saw several investors take a step back from the biopharma scene. Credits: AFP</i>
          </p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
           After going public via <a 
style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #8C3321; color: black;" href="https://link.businesshistory.co/bh-28-06-2025-spac" target="_blank">SPAC</a> in 2021, its valuation soared temporarily but plummeted due to rising interests, weak revenue from kit trade, and losses in its therapeutic R&D efforts. In 2023, news broke that <a 
style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #8C3321; color: black;" href="https://link.businesshistory.co/bh-28-06-2025-hackers-had-obtained" target="_blank">hackers had obtained</a> the profiles of 6.9Mn people. This led to a reported $667M loss and shut down drug development. 
            </p>
            <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
           Pivoting to telehealth and launching an Ozempic-based weight-loss program via Lemonaid Health didn’t reverse its fortunes. With share values hovering near delisting levels, 23andMe announced a reverse stock split to stay afloat. While 23andMe has pledged to maintain its privacy policy, who will gain permission to all the abundant genetic data of customers if the company is sold is unclear. 
            </p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column> 
